<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 04 at 7:45PM EST  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...SLICK ROADS IN THE WAKE OF LIGHT SNOW AND LOW TEMPERATURES...
Light snow having left a coating to a quick fluffy inch this
evening, together with temperatures falling through the lower 20s,
have likely caused road surfaces to refreeze, including ice hidden
beneath the snow. Spotty freezing drizzle or mist could make
surfaces even more slippery.
Be prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Allow extra time when
traveling, slow down and leave plenty of extra space between your
vehicle and the one in front of you.</description>
